body_description: The purpose of this Committee is to serve, foster, and strengthen community by providing access to lifelong learning, opportunities to enjoy life, ensuring a diverse range of housing opportunities, and preserving healthy neighborhoods.

The purpose of this Committee is to manage growth and change of the City in order to encourage a strong economy; ensure a diverse range of arts, cultural, and entertainment offerings; and create and preserve housing and healthy neighborhoods.

body_name: Smart Cities and Service Improvements Committee
Public Safety, Finance and Strategic Support Committee (PSFSS)
body_description: The purpose of the PSFSS Committee is to effectively develop, manage, and safeguard the City's fiscal, physical, technological, and human resources to enable and enhance the delivery of City services and projects and to provide prevention and emergency response services for crime, fire, medical, hazardous, and disaster related situations.

Joint Meeting for the Rules and Open Government Committee and Committee of the Whole
AD-HOC Committee for Housing Construction & Development Services
body_description: Meetings will be held the 4th Thursday of every other month from 9:00 a.m. to 10:30 a.m. in the Committee Rooms W118-120. Their purpose is to address: Key Process Improvements, including updating performance metrics, creating a development services dashboard, and implementing change management, cost of service study adjustments, and code reform programs; Update on Development Services staffing, filled positions and vacancies; Status Report on Major Development Projects in Entitlement and Construction Process; and, Customer/Public Feedback.
The committee administers the Deferred Compensation Plan
